{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PqXAwKJU9eRo18mHPV3ByX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**State found:** MongoDB was running with `--auth --keyFile` but no users existed. Three users were pre-created in the admin db with incorrect/incomplete roles (`app-user` had only `read`, `readonly-user` had only `read`, both missing the required permissions).\n\n**Steps taken:**\n\n1. **Temporarily removed `--auth --keyFile`** from the StatefulSet to use the unauthenticated localhost path, created the `admin` superuser, then restored `--auth --keyFile`.\n\n2. **Created `reportingRole`** in `appdb` — grants `find` on `appdb.reports` (sufficient for `aggregate()`).\n\n3. **Fixed `app-user`** (admin auth db): revoked `read`, granted `readWrite` on `appdb`.\n\n4. **Fixed `readonly-user`** (admin auth db): kept `read` on `appdb`, added `reportingRole` on `appdb`.\n\n**Verified:**\n- `app-user` (password `app123password`) — can insert + query in `appdb` ✓\n- `readonly-user` (password `readonly123password`) — `aggregate()` on `appdb.reports` succeeds, writes are denied ✓\n- `admin-user` (password `admin123password`) — full admin access intact, replica set healthy (1 primary, 2 secondaries) ✓"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":378,"cache_read_input_tokens":56958,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":378},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bad8c33f-b20b-48fc-85af-58aef730b2c8","uuid":"e6ab99b4-e007-4ab4-961c-9eed8acdfa0f","request_id":"req_011CcPpRpF4UBY2yd3EvEa6Q"}
